\begin_layout Subsection*
Case 1: Shutting down the network effectively stops the contaminant beyond
 the actuator too.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In this simpler case, there are no additional constraints on the actuator
 placement problem beyond the being a min-cut of the entire graph.
 The sensor and actuator placement problems are independent.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As long as the sensor network can detect the contaminant before it reaches
 the demands and the actuation can happen simultaneously, the requirements
 are satisfied.
\end_layout

